<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FDDFE5348A75693FE2BFC5C" pageId="403" pageNumber="404" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418FDDFE5348A75693FEC7FC77" blockId="403.[151,1437,447,1156]" pageId="403" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FDDFE5348A75693FE31FE28" bold="true" box="[151,404,447,472]" pageId="403" pageNumber="404">Description of female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FDDFE5349945693FD84FE27" box="[420,545,447,471]" captionStart="PLATE 126" captionStartId="404.[151,233,1907,1930]" captionTargetBox="[223,1353,184,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-96@404.[181,1386,163,1906]" captionTargetPageId="404" captionText="PLATE 126. A. Dorsal view. Length 7.5 mm. B, D, E. Heads. C. Mesosoma. F. Chela. A–C, F. Gonatopus cristatus (=Megagonatopus birmanus Olmi &amp; Currado, 1976), female from Myanmar (from Olmi &amp; Currado, 1976). D, E. Gonatopus daunus, holotype, frontal view (D) and dorsal view (E) (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 2.27 mm for B, 1.55 mm for C, 0.94 mm for D and E, 0.36 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278816" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278816/files/figure.png" pageId="403" pageNumber="404">Plate 126A</figureCitation>
): apterous; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48FDDFE534AC15693FCDEFE27" box="[753,891,447,471]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.85" metricValueMax="7.5" metricValueMin="6.2" pageId="403" pageNumber="404" unit="mm" value="6.85" valueMax="7.5" valueMin="6.2">6.2–7.5 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible and lateral regions of clypeus yellow; antenna black, in some specimens with segment 1 brown-yellow; mesoosma and metasoma black; legs black, except tarsi testaceous; in some specimens coxae, clubs of femora and tibiae reddish. Antenna clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 17:10:36:30:22:22:20:16:14:15. Head (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FDDFE534D3A5500FA37FDB4" box="[1290,1426,556,580]" captionStart="PLATE 126" captionStartId="404.[151,233,1907,1930]" captionTargetBox="[223,1353,184,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-96@404.[181,1386,163,1906]" captionTargetPageId="404" captionText="PLATE 126. A. Dorsal view. Length 7.5 mm. B, D, E. Heads. C. Mesosoma. F. Chela. A–C, F. Gonatopus cristatus (=Megagonatopus birmanus Olmi &amp; Currado, 1976), female from Myanmar (from Olmi &amp; Currado, 1976). D, E. Gonatopus daunus, holotype, frontal view (D) and dorsal view (E) (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 2.27 mm for B, 1.55 mm for C, 0.94 mm for D and E, 0.36 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278816" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278816/files/figure.png" pageId="403" pageNumber="404">Plate 126B</figureCitation>
) excavated, shiny, smooth, unsculptured; occipital carina absent. Palpal formula 6/3. Pronotum shiny, smooth, unsculptured, crossed by strong transverse impression, with disc not regularly rounded, but posteriorly compressed into median longitudinal carina. Scutum dull, sculptured by some longitudinal keels. Metanotum transversely striate. Metathorax + propodeum (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FDDFE534A1B5590FD09FD24" box="[555,684,700,724]" captionStart="PLATE 126" captionStartId="404.[151,233,1907,1930]" captionTargetBox="[223,1353,184,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-96@404.[181,1386,163,1906]" captionTargetPageId="404" captionText="PLATE 126. A. Dorsal view. Length 7.5 mm. B, D, E. Heads. C. Mesosoma. F. Chela. A–C, F. Gonatopus cristatus (=Megagonatopus birmanus Olmi &amp; Currado, 1976), female from Myanmar (from Olmi &amp; Currado, 1976). D, E. Gonatopus daunus, holotype, frontal view (D) and dorsal view (E) (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 2.27 mm for B, 1.55 mm for C, 0.94 mm for D and E, 0.36 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278816" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278816/files/figure.png" pageId="403" pageNumber="404">Plate 126C</figureCitation>
) shiny, with anterior surface unsculptured and posterior surface transversely striate. Mesopleuron and metapleuron transversely striate. Meso-metapleural obsolete. Protarsal segments in following proportions: 26:4:10:32:46. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FDDFE534BB85428FBA4FCEC" box="[904,1025,772,796]" captionStart="PLATE 126" captionStartId="404.[151,233,1907,1930]" captionTargetBox="[223,1353,184,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-96@404.[181,1386,163,1906]" captionTargetPageId="404" captionText="PLATE 126. A. Dorsal view. Length 7.5 mm. B, D, E. Heads. C. Mesosoma. F. Chela. A–C, F. Gonatopus cristatus (=Megagonatopus birmanus Olmi &amp; Currado, 1976), female from Myanmar (from Olmi &amp; Currado, 1976). D, E. Gonatopus daunus, holotype, frontal view (D) and dorsal view (E) (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 2.27 mm for B, 1.55 mm for C, 0.94 mm for D and E, 0.36 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278816" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278816/files/figure.png" pageId="403" pageNumber="404">Plate 126F</figureCitation>
) with one small subapical tooth and one row of eight peg-like hairs. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FDDFE534B29540BFC37FCCF" box="[793,914,807,831]" captionStart="PLATE 126" captionStartId="404.[151,233,1907,1930]" captionTargetBox="[223,1353,184,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-96@404.[181,1386,163,1906]" captionTargetPageId="404" captionText="PLATE 126. A. Dorsal view. Length 7.5 mm. B, D, E. Heads. C. Mesosoma. F. Chela. A–C, F. Gonatopus cristatus (=Megagonatopus birmanus Olmi &amp; Currado, 1976), female from Myanmar (from Olmi &amp; Currado, 1976). D, E. Gonatopus daunus, holotype, frontal view (D) and dorsal view (E) (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 2.27 mm for B, 1.55 mm for C, 0.94 mm for D and E, 0.36 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278816" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278816/files/figure.png" pageId="403" pageNumber="404">Plate 126F</figureCitation>
) with inner side proximally not serrated, with two rows of 36–46 lamellae beginning in proximal third of segment 5; distal apex with at least 15–17 lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/0/1.
</paragraph>
